<h2>Installation</h2>

<p>Because no two testers are alike, Dradis is cross-platform, it runs in <a href="http://guides.dradisframework.org/install_on_ubuntu.html">Linux</a>, <a href="http://guides.dradisframework.org/install_on_macos.html">Mac</a>, <a href="http://guides.dradisframework.org/install_on_freebsd.html">FreeBSD</a> and <a href="http://downloads.sourceforge.net/dradis/dradis-v2.9.0-setup.exe">Windows</a>, and you just need a web browser to talk to it. The latest version of Dradis is also bundled with <a href="http://www.kali.org/">Kali</a>, so if you are considering giving Dradis a try, that's probably the easiest way to get up and running.</p>


